    "summary": "Repair #97802 by updating the new numeric-options tests to satisfy lint: replace global NaN literals with Number.NaN, then rerun the focused test and changed gate. Preserve dwc1997's contributor PR as the source branch because maintainers can modify it.",
    "pr_title": "test(infra): repair numeric option helper test lint",
    "pr_body": "What Problem This Solves\n\nRepairs #97802 so the new numeric option helper coverage can pass lint and proceed to merge preflight.\n\nWhy This Change Was Made\n\nThe hydrated ClawSweeper review and CI show the submitted head fails check-lint because the new tests use global NaN literals. The narrow repair is to use Number.NaN in the added test file while preserving the contributor's test coverage.\n\nUser Impact\n\nNo runtime behavior changes. This keeps focused regression coverage for numeric CLI/config option helper behavior.\n\nEvidence\n\nPlanned validation: node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/numeric-options.test.ts and pnpm check:changed.\n\nCredit\n\nThis repair carries forward @dwc1997's source PR: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/97802.",
    "likely_files": [
      "src/infra/numeric-options.test.ts"
    ],
